    "To address homology issues, proteins sharing over 30% sequence identity with the test proteins were excluded from the training dataset 45.",
    "The remaining proteins were utilized to construct databases for BLAST and FunFams.",
    "95% of them were randomly selected for training DeepGO, ATGO+, SPROF-GO, and PhiGnet, with the remaining 5% reserved for validation to fine-tune the methods' parameters.",
    "Moreover, we conducted comparisons among the different methods using the CAFA3 test proteins either with less than 60% sequence identity to those in the training dataset or without redundancy removal (Supplementary Fig.",
    "A comparison among the six different methods implemented on the CAFA3 dataset reveals that PhiGnet exhibits the best performance across both F max and AUPR metrics (Table 1, Supplementary Fig."
